      <section id="market-changes" class="py-12">
        <div class="gradient-border mb-8"></div>
        <h2 class="serif-heading text-3xl font-bold mb-8">What Has Changed in the Merchant Services Market</h2>

        <div class="mb-8">
          <h3 class="serif-heading text-2xl font-semibold mb-6">Card Scheme and Processing Fees</h3>

          <div class="mb-6">
            <h4 class="font-bold text-lg mb-4">PSR Findings on Scheme Fee Increases</h4>
            <p class="mb-4">
              The Payment Systems Regulator&#39;s market review represents the most authoritative assessment of UK payment cost dynamics. The PSR found that <strong>competition between Visa and Mastercard is weaker than expected</strong>, with both schemes able to increase fees without sufficient competitive pressure <a href="#ref-8" class="citation">[8]</a>.
            </p>

            <div class="data-table mb-6">
              <table class="w-full">
                <thead>
                  <tr>
                    <th>Period</th>
                    <th>Scheme</th>
                    <th>Fee Change</th>
                    <th>Impact</th>
                  </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                  <tr>
                    <td>2018-2023</td>
                    <td>Both</td>
                    <td>~30% real terms increase</td>
                    <td>PSR-documented cost pressure</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td><strong>January 2026</strong></td>
                    <td><strong>Both</strong></td>
                    <td><strong>Cross-border debit ~300%; credit ~200%</strong></td>
                    <td><strong>Immediate cost pressure on international transactions</strong></td>
                  </tr>
                </tbody>
              </table>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="mb-6">
            <h4 class="font-bold text-lg mb-4">Impact on Merchant Pricing</h4>
            <p class="mb-4">
              Scheme fee pressure affects merchant pricing through a cascade mechanism that disproportionately impacts smaller businesses. SMEs on blended rates face opaque incorporation of scheme fee rises with limited ability to challenge or compare <a href="#ref-8" class="citation">[8]</a>
              <a href="#ref-11" class="citation">[11]</a>.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="mb-8">
          <h3 class="serif-heading text-2xl font-semibold mb-6">Provider Cost Pressures</h3>

          <div class="mb-6">
            <h4 class="font-bold text-lg mb-4">Acquirer Margin Compression</h4>
            <p class="mb-4">
              Acquirers face structural margin squeeze from regulated interchange income and rising scheme fee costs. The European Payfac/ISV pricing analysis notes that with tight transaction margins, providers <strong>&#34;must think beyond payments&#34;</strong> and bundle with SaaS, analytics, and financial services to maintain profitability <a href="#ref-128" class="citation">[128]</a>.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="mb-6">
            <h4 class="font-bold text-lg mb-4">Regulatory Compliance Costs</h4>
            <div class="data-table">
              <table class="w-full">
                <thead>
                  <tr>
                    <th>Regulatory Development</th>
                    <th>Implementation</th>
                    <th>Provider Cost Impact</th>
                  </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                  <tr>
                    <td>APP fraud reimbursement regime</td>
                    <td>October 2024</td>
                    <td>Direct reimbursement liability; fraud prevention investment</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td>PCI DSS v4.0.1</td>
                    <td>Transition 2024-2025</td>
                    <td>Security infrastructure; assessment procedures</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr>
                    <td>PSD2 Strong Customer Authentication</td>
                    <td>Enforced March 2022</td>
                    <td>3D Secure infrastructure; exemption management</td>
                  </tr>
                </tbody>
              </table>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="mb-8">
          <h3 class="serif-heading text-2xl font-semibold mb-6">Payment Behaviour Shifts</h3>

          <div class="mb-6">
            <h4 class="font-bold text-lg mb-4">Contactless and Digital Wallet Dominance</h4>
            <p class="mb-4">
              UK payment behaviour has undergone structural transformation. Barclays 2024 data shows <strong>94.5% of eligible in-store card transactions were contactless</strong>
              <a href="#ref-100" class="citation">[100]</a>. The ECB&#39;s SPACE study confirms this extends to low-value transactions previously dominated by cash.
            </p>

            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mb-6">
              <img src="https://kimi-web-img.moonshot.cn/img/www.poszeo.com/1fdc55c395fadd5b60f6ac0e9d3875c5c7aa1a77.webp" alt="Customer using contactless payment at retail terminal" class="rounded-lg" size="medium" aspect="wide" style="photo" query="contactless payment terminal" referrerpolicy="no-referrer" data-modified="1" data-score="0.00"/>
