      <!-- Hidden Cost Problem -->
      <section id="hidden-costs" class="py-12">
        <div class="gradient-border mb-8"></div>
        <h2 class="serif-heading text-3xl font-bold mb-8">The Hidden Cost Problem</h2>

        <div class="mb-8">
          <h3 class="serif-heading text-2xl font-semibold mb-6">Why Headline Rates Mislead</h3>

          <div class="highlight-box mb-6">
            <h4 class="font-bold text-lg mb-3">Effective Rate Formula</h4>
            <div class="text-center text-xl font-mono bg-black/20 p-4 rounded">
              Effective Rate = Total Fees Paid ÷ Total Card Turnover × 100%
            </div>
          </div>

          <p class="mb-4">
            The headline transaction rate systematically understates true payment acceptance costs. This is not accidental deception but structural feature of a market where acquisition competition focuses on the most visible metric while profitability is recovered through less visible components.
          </p>

          <div class="data-table mb-6">
            <table class="w-full">
              <thead>
                <tr>
                  <th>Merchant Profile</th>
                  <th>Headline Rate</th>
                  <th>Effective Rate</th>
                  <th>Gap</th>
                </tr>
              </thead>
              <tbody>
                <tr>
